"Iron Hammer" Lang Ping to coach China women's national volleyball team
2013-04-25 02:42:41 GMT
By Jia Xiaoguang, Sina EnglishLang Ping, former Chinese volleyball superstar nicknamed “Iron Hammer”, is formally appointed as the head coach of China women’s national team, according to the official announcement by the Volleyball Sport Administrative Center on April 25.The appointment marks the start of the second tenure of Lang, now aged 53, as the chief of the beloved women’s national volleyball team after 1995. With the expertise as both previous player and coach, she is expected to steer the squad she used to figure in away from the current stalemate and compete as a candidate for a medal in the 2016 Rio de Janeiro Olympics.
